HEB1420 | Human Evolutionary Anatomy | http://www.courses.fas.harvard.edu/6233 | instructors: Tanya M. Smith prereq:Life Sciences 2 or with permission of instructor. term:Half course (spring term). M., W., F., at 10, and a weekly section to be arranged. EXAM GROUP:   5 description:How did the human body evolve, and how does it develop, grow and function?   This course provides an integrative regional overview of human anatomy, with an emphasis on the musculo-skeletal system, and a comparative approach to the evolution of modern anatomy.  Additional topics include: skeletal and dental development; gross anatomy of the nervous and circulatory systems; comparative limb anatomy; and comparative cranial anatomy. 
